abstract: It turns out that today's cycad plants originated only about 10 million years ago, not when dinosaurs roamed the earth, a new study says.
snippet: It turns out that today's cycad plants originated only about 10 million years ago, not when dinosaurs roamed the earth, a new study says.
lead_paragraph: Modern-day cycads that were assumed to have existed when dinosaurs roamed the earth over 200 million years ago are actually far younger, researchers report. [The Times of London]

headline.main: On Our Radar: 'Living Fossil' Is Younger Than Thought
